parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the lack of supplemental restraint can exacerbate the severity of the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelts to hold occupants in place can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may be thrown from their seats or collide with interior components.
symptoms: Seatbelts fail to restrain occupants
resulting in injuries or fatalities
and may be accompanied by airbag failure to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seats to remain upright and secure can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as occupants may be thrown from their seats or collide with interior components.
symptoms: Bucket seats collapse backwards
touching rear bench seats
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinges can cause the door to fall off the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries, and making it difficult or impossible to close the door properly.
symptoms: The door becomes difficult to close
the door hangs down when opened
the door does not close or seal properly
the door rubs against the quarter panel
the hinge seizes up
the bracket bends or structurally fails
the door falls off the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle speed control motor can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle will not idle
the vehicle cuts out when coming to a stop
the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioner compressor can cause the compressor to blow a pressure valve, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The air conditioner stops working
the compressor blows a pressure valve.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as emotional distress and economic losses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when applying little pressure to the gas pedal
hesitates and then surges forward
or accelerates and surges forward or backward when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion in the fuel injectors can cause issues with the vehicle's performance, including unintended acceleration, and may lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience hesitation
surging
or sudden acceleration
and may have corrosion in the fuel injectors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the timing or serpentine belts can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience engine problems
hesitation
or surging
and may require replacement of the timing or serpentine belts.
